{"title_page": "Uwe Tellkamp", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2014}}\n{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] -->\n| name = Uwe Tellkamp\n| image = Uwe Tellkamp Worms.jpg\n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1968|10|28}}\n| birth_place = [[Dresden]], East Germany\n| occupation = Novelist, physician\n| nationality = German\n| genre =\n| subject =\n| movement =\n| notableworks = ''Der Turm''\n| influences = \n| influenced = \n| awards = {{awd|[[German Book Prize]]|2008}}\n}}\n\n'''Uwe Tellkamp''' (born October 28, 1968 in [[Dresden]], [[East Germany]]) is a German writer and physician. He practised medicine until 2004. Before the [[fall of communism]], he was enlisted in the [[National People's Army]] as a tank commander and imprisoned when he refused to break up a demonstration in October 1989.<ref>Philipp Engel: ''Uwe Tellkamp, Bestseller-Autor und Gewinner des Deutschen Buchpreises \u00fcber die DDR, den Finanzkapitalismus, das Schreiben und sein n\u00e4chstes Buch''. Interview vom 17. Februar 2009. http://www.ruhrbarone.de/uwe-tellkamp-bestseller-autor-und-gewinner-des-deutschen-buchpreises-uber-die-ddr-den-finanzkapitalismus-das-schreiben-und-sein-nachstes-buch/</ref> Until the fall of the [[German Democratic Republic]] shortly after, he was prohibited from studying medicine.\n\nIn 2008 Tellkamp was awarded the [[German Book Prize]] for his novel ''Der Turm'' (The Tower), which describes life in 1980s [[East Germany]].<ref>{{cite news |title=What was the GDR? |author=Jane Yager |newspaper=[[The Sunday Times]] |date=December 31, 2008 |url=http://entertainment.timesonline.co.uk/tol/arts_and_entertainment/the_tls/article5423569.ece |accessdate=September 26, 2010}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017 Tellkamp signed the \"Charta 2017\", criticizing the [[ostracism]] of [[Neue Rechte|'New Right']] publishers at the [[Leipzig]] book fair (\"[[Leipziger Buchmesse]]\").<ref>{{cite web|title=Susanne Dagen reagiert mit einer \"Charta 2017\" auf die Buchmesse-Vorf\u00e4lle / \"Nicht mehr weit von einer Gesinnungsdiktatur entfernt\"|periodical=B\u00f6rsenblatt|url=https://www.boersenblatt.net/artikel-susanne_dagen_reagiert_mit_einer__charta_2017__auf_die_buchmesse-vorfaelle.1390030.html|accessdate=2018-03-16|date=2017-10-17|language=German}}</ref><ref>[https://www.openpetition.de/petition/online/charta-2017-zu-den-vorkommnissen-auf-der-frankfurter-buchmesse-2017 Appell: Charta 2017 - Zu den Vorkommnissen auf der Frankfurter Buchmesse 2017] Wortlaut Charta 2017 auf openpetition.de</ref><ref name=\":0\" />\n\nPreceding the [[Leipziger Buchmesse]] 2018 Tellkamp said:<ref name=\":1\">{{citation|surname1=Durs Gr\u00fcnbein|periodical=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|title=Die s\u00fc\u00dfe Krankheit Dresden|page=11|date=2018-03-14|language=German\n}}</ref> \n\"Most [refugees] are not trying to escape war and prosecution but come [to Germany] to migrate into the social support system, more than 95%.\"<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|title=Suhrkamp-Verlag distanziert sich von Uwe Tellkamp |periodical=Deutsche Welle |url=http://p.dw.com/p/2u23f |accessdate=2018-03-13 |authors=dpa, kna, epd|date=2018-03-09 |language=German}}&#32;The [https://twitter.com/suhrkamp/status/972035792003616769 Tweet] of [[Suhrkamp]] publishing house: \u201eAus gegebenem Anlass: Die Haltung, die in \u00c4u\u00dferungen von Autoren des Hauses zum Ausdruck kommt, ist nicht mit der des Verlags zu verwechseln. #Tellkamp\u201c</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Umstrittene \u00c4u\u00dferungen Uwe Tellkamps/ Suhrkamp geht auf Distanz |periodical=B\u00f6rsenblatt |url=https://www.boersenblatt.net/artikel-umstrittene___usserungen_uwe_tellkamps.1439190.html |accessdate=2018-03-15|date=2018-03-09 |language=German}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2018 he signed the \"Joint Statement 2018\" (\"Gemeinsame Erkl\u00e4rung 2018\"), declaring: \"We observe the damage done to [[Germany]] by illegal mass immigration with growing disconcertment. We declare our solidarity with those who are peacefully rallying for the restoration of the constitutional order at the borders of our country.\"\u201c<ref>{{cite web |periodical=S\u00e4chsische Zeitung |title=Tellkamp unterzeichnet Erkl\u00e4rung |date=2017-03-17 |language=German |url=http://www.sz-online.de/nachrichten/kultur/tellkamp-unterzeichnet-erklaerung-3899858.html |trans-title=Tellkamp Signs Statement |access-date=2018-03-17 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180316234219/http://www.sz-online.de/nachrichten/kultur/tellkamp-unterzeichnet-erklaerung-3899858.html |archive-date=2018-03-16}} vgl. zum Wortlaut der {{cite web |url=https://erklaerung2018.de/ |title=Gemeinsamen Erkl\u00e4rung |date=2018-03-15 |language=German |trans-title=Joint Statement}}</ref><ref>Andreas Montag, [https://www.mz-web.de/kultur/neue-nationale-front--gemeinsame-erklaerung--von-kuenstlern-und-intellektuellen-29889910 Neue Nationale Front \u201eGemeinsame Erkl\u00e4rung\u201c von K\u00fcnstlern und Intellektuellen], Mitteldeutsche Zeitung online, 19. M\u00e4rz 2018.</ref><ref>Christian Schr\u00f6der: [https://www.tagesspiegel.de/kultur/erklaerung-2018-uwe-tellkamp-fuer-solidaritaet-gegen-einwanderer/21088232.html ''Uwe Tellkamp f\u00fcr Solidarit\u00e4t gegen Einwanderer''], Tagesspiegel vom 20. M\u00e4rz 2018</ref><ref name=\"ndr-018114\">{{cite web|title=Wie brisant ist die \"Erkl\u00e4rung 2018\"?|periodical=ndr.de|url=https://www.ndr.de/kultur/Wie-brisant-ist-die-Erklaerung-2018,erklaerung114.html|accessdate=2018-03-29|last=Ndr|date=2018-03-27|language=German}}</ref>\n\n== Works ==\n* ''Der Hecht, die Tr\u00e4ume und das Portugiesische Caf\u00e9'' (2000)\n* ''Der Eisvogel'' (2005)\n* ''Der Turm'' (2008)\n* ''Reise zur Blauen Stadt'' (2009)\n* ''Die Schwebebahn: Dresdner Erkundungen'' (2012)\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tellkamp, Uwe}}\n[[Category:1968 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century German novelists]]\n[[Category:Ingeborg Bachmann Prize winners]]\n[[Category:German male novelists]]\n[[Category:German medical writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century German male writers]]\n[[Category:German Book Prize winners]]\n[[Category:German male non-fiction writers]]\n\n\n{{Germany-writer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2014}}\n{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] -->\n| name = Uwe Tellkamp\n| image = Uwe Tellkamp Worms.jpg\n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1968|10|28}}\n| birth_place = [[Dresden]], East Germany\n| occupation = Novelist, physician\n| nationality = German\n| genre =\n| subject =\n| movement =\n| notableworks = ''Der Turm''\n| influences = \n| influenced = \n| awards = {{awd|[[German Book Prize]]|2008}}\n}}\n\n'''Uwe Tellkamp''' (born October 28, 1968 in [[Dresden]], [[East Germany]]) is a German writer and physician. He practised medicine until 2004. Before the [[fall of communism]], he was enlisted in the [[National People's Army]] as a tank commander and imprisoned when he refused to break up a demonstration in October 1989.<ref>Philipp Engel: ''Uwe Tellkamp, Bestseller-Autor und Gewinner des Deutschen Buchpreises \u00fcber die DDR, den Finanzkapitalismus, das Schreiben und sein n\u00e4chstes Buch''. Interview vom 17. Februar 2009. http://www.ruhrbarone.de/uwe-tellkamp-bestseller-autor-und-gewinner-des-deutschen-buchpreises-uber-die-ddr-den-finanzkapitalismus-das-schreiben-und-sein-nachstes-buch/</ref> Until the fall of the [[German Democratic Republic]] shortly after, he was prohibited from studying medicine.\n\nIn 2008 Tellkamp was awarded the [[German Book Prize]] for his novel ''Der Turm'' (The Tower), which describes life in 1980s [[East Germany]].<ref>{{cite news |title=What was the GDR? |author=Jane Yager |newspaper=[[The Sunday Times]] |date=December 31, 2008 |url=http://entertainment.timesonline.co.uk/tol/arts_and_entertainment/the_tls/article5423569.ece |accessdate=September 26, 2010}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017 Tellkamp signed the \"Charta 2017\", criticizing the [[ostracism]] of [[Neue Rechte|'New Right']] publishers at the [[Leipzig]] book fair (\"[[Leipziger Buchmesse]]\").<ref>{{cite web|title=Susanne Dagen reagiert mit einer \"Charta 2017\" auf die Buchmesse-Vorf\u00e4lle / \"Nicht mehr weit von einer Gesinnungsdiktatur entfernt\"|periodical=B\u00f6rsenblatt|url=https://www.boersenblatt.net/artikel-susanne_dagen_reagiert_mit_einer__charta_2017__auf_die_buchmesse-vorfaelle.1390030.html|accessdate=2018-03-16|date=2017-10-17|language=German}}</ref><ref>[https://www.openpetition.de/petition/online/charta-2017-zu-den-vorkommnissen-auf-der-frankfurter-buchmesse-2017 Appell: Charta 2017 - Zu den Vorkommnissen auf der Frankfurter Buchmesse 2017] Wortlaut Charta 2017 auf openpetition.de</ref><ref name=\":0\" />\n\nPreceding the [[Leipziger Buchmesse]] 2018 Tellkamp said:<ref name=\":1\">{{citation|surname1=Durs Gr\u00fcnbein|periodical=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|title=Die s\u00fc\u00dfe Krankheit Dresden|page=11|date=2018-03-14|language=German\n}}</ref> \n\"Most [refugees] are not trying to escape war and prosecution but come [to Germany] to migrate into the social support system, more than 95%.\"<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|title=Suhrkamp-Verlag distanziert sich von Uwe Tellkamp |periodical=Deutsche Welle |url=http://p.dw.com/p/2u23f |accessdate=2018-03-13 |authors=dpa, kna, epd|date=2018-03-09 |language=German}}&#32;The [https://twitter.com/suhrkamp/status/972035792003616769 Tweet] of [[Suhrkamp]] publishing house: \u201eAus gegebenem Anlass: Die Haltung, die in \u00c4u\u00dferungen von Autoren des Hauses zum Ausdruck kommt, ist nicht mit der des Verlags zu verwechseln. #Tellkamp\u201c</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Umstrittene \u00c4u\u00dferungen Uwe Tellkamps/ Suhrkamp geht auf Distanz |periodical=B\u00f6rsenblatt |url=https://www.boersenblatt.net/artikel-umstrittene___usserungen_uwe_tellkamps.1439190.html |accessdate=2018-03-15|date=2018-03-09 |language=German}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2018 he signed the \"Joint Statement 2018\" (\"Gemeinsame Erkl\u00e4rung 2018\"), declaring: \"We observe the damage done to [[Germany]] by illegal mass immigration with growing disconcertment. We declare our solidarity with those who are peacefully rallying for the restoration of the constitutional order at the borders of our country.\"\u201c<ref>{{cite web |periodical=S\u00e4chsische Zeitung |title=Tellkamp unterzeichnet Erkl\u00e4rung |date=2017-03-17 |language=German |url=http://www.sz-online.de/nachrichten/kultur/tellkamp-unterzeichnet-erklaerung-3899858.html |trans-title=Tellkamp Signs Statement |access-date=2018-03-17 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180316234219/http://www.sz-online.de/nachrichten/kultur/tellkamp-unterzeichnet-erklaerung-3899858.html |archive-date=2018-03-16}} vgl. zum Wortlaut der {{cite web |url=https://erklaerung2018.de/ |title=Gemeinsamen Erkl\u00e4rung |date=2018-03-15 |language=German |trans-title=Joint Statement}}</ref><ref>Andreas Montag, [https://www.mz-web.de/kultur/neue-nationale-front--gemeinsame-erklaerung--von-kuenstlern-und-intellektuellen-29889910 Neue Nationale Front \u201eGemeinsame Erkl\u00e4rung\u201c von K\u00fcnstlern und Intellektuellen], Mitteldeutsche Zeitung online, 19. M\u00e4rz 2018.</ref><ref>Christian Schr\u00f6der: [https://www.tagesspiegel.de/kultur/erklaerung-2018-uwe-tellkamp-fuer-solidaritaet-gegen-einwanderer/21088232.html ''Uwe Tellkamp f\u00fcr Solidarit\u00e4t gegen Einwanderer''], Tagesspiegel vom 20. M\u00e4rz 2018</ref><ref name=\"ndr-018114\">{{cite web|title=Wie brisant ist die \"Erkl\u00e4rung 2018\"?|periodical=ndr.de|url=https://www.ndr.de/kultur/Wie-brisant-ist-die-Erklaerung-2018,erklaerung114.html|accessdate=2018-03-29|last=Ndr|date=2018-03-27|language=German}}</ref>\n\n== Works ==\n* ''Der Hecht, die Tr\u00e4ume und das Portugiesische Caf\u00e9'' (2000)\n* ''Der Eisvogel'' (2005)\n* ''Der Turm'' (2008)\n* ''Reise zur Blauen Stadt'' (2009)\n* ''Die Schwebebahn: Dresdner Erkundungen'' (2012)\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tellkamp, Uwe}}\n[[Category:1968 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century German novelists]]\n[[Category:Ingeborg Bachmann Prize winners]]\n[[Category:German male novelists]]\n[[Category:German medical writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male writers]]\n[[Category:German Book Prize winners]]\n[[Category:German male non-fiction writers]]\n\n\n{{Germany-writer-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Bearcat", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:recat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uwe_Tellkamp"}
{"title_page": "TrueMoney", "text_new": "{{COI|date=September 2016}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name                = TrueMoney\n| logo                = TMN-LOGO.jpg\n| logo_size           = 300px\n| type                = [[Privately held company]]\n| area_served         = 6 countries across Southeast Asia: Thailand, Cambodia, Myanmar, Vietnam, Indonesia and Philippines (as of 2019)\n| key_people          = Smile key\n| services            = [[e-payment]]<br>[[mobile payment]]<br>[[digital banking]]\n| industry            = [[Fintech]], [[Financial Services]]\n| num_employees       = 700-1000\n| parent              = [[Asia Group]]<br>[[Asia Money]]\n| foundation          = 2020\n| location            = Bangkok, Thailand\n| website             = {{URL|http://www.ascendmoney.io|Ascend Money}}\n<br>{{URL|http://www.truemoney.com|TrueMoney Thailand}}<br>{{URL|http://www.truemoney.com.ph|TrueMoney Philippines}}<br>{{URL|http://www.truemoney.com.kh|TrueMoney Cambodia}}<br>{{URL|http://www.truemoney.co.id|TrueMoney Indonesia}}<br>{{URL|http://truemoneymyanmar.com/|TrueMoney Myanmar}}<br>{{URL|https://truemoney.com.vn/|TrueMoney Vietnam}}\n| True phone          = True phone\n}}\n\n'''TrueMoney''' is a financial technology company in Southeast Asia with a mission to enable everyone to have access to financial services. \n\nThe company serves both digital and non digital customers in Thailand, Cambodia, Myanmar, Vietnam, Philippines, and Indonesia. TrueMoney has licenses to operate e-money in most Southeast Asian country.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bangkokpost.com/business/telecom/530175/true-money-makes-regional-moves|title=True Money makes regional moves &#124; Bangkok Post: business|date=2015-04-16|publisher=Bangkokpost.com|accessdate=2015-06-25}}</ref> \n\nOperated by its parent company Ascend Money and in partnership with Ant Financial (a subsidiary of Alibaba Group).\n\nAs of May 2019, the total processed value (TPV) of TrueMoney company was US$ 7.3 billion.\n\n==History==\nTrueMoney was originally founded in 2003 as part of [https://www3.truecorp.co.th/new/?ln=en True Corporation], but presently is operated by [https://www.ascendmoney.io/ Ascend Money] company, a subsidiary of [https://www.ascendcorp.com/ Ascend Group] - the digital technology arm of [http://www.cpgroupglobal.com/ Charoen Pokphand Group].  \n\nSince 1st November 2016, Ant Financial (Alipay) company invested in Ascend Money company.         This partnership aims to grow TrueMoney's technical expertise to strengthen its financial services eco-system for users and merchants<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2016/11/01/ant-financial-invests-in-thailands-ascent-money-as-part-of-global-expansion-play.html|title=Ant Financial invests in Thailand's Ascend Money as part of global expansion play|last=Choudhury|first=Saheli Roy|date=2016-11-01|website=CNBC|language=en|access-date=2019-06-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nationmultimedia.com/detail/Economy/30298894|title=Ascend Money links with Alibaba financial services unit|website=The Nation|language=en|access-date=2019-06-06}}</ref>\n\n==Services==\nIn Thailand, TrueMoney operates the \"TrueMoney Wallet\" brand (e-wallet application) that enable users to easily make online and offline payments (e.g. mobile/net top-ups, gaming top-ups, bill payments, peer-to-peer transfers, and QR-bar code scan retail payments) via using mobile phones.\n\nAs of 2019, the number of TrueMoney Wallet active annual users reached 8.4 million. \n\nBy leveraging on the brand's partnerships (e.g. 7-Eleven, popular F&B chains, online marketplace, street food vendors, etc), and world-class digital technology partners (e.g. Google<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bangkokpost.com/tech/local-news/1653488/truemoney-teams-up-with-google-play|title=TrueMoney teams up with Google Play|last=Limited|first=Bangkok Post Public Company|website=https://www.bangkokpost.com|access-date=2019-06-06}}</ref>, Apple<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.appdisqus.com/2017/12/21/truemoney-wallet-app-store-ios.html|title=\u0e0b\u0e37\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e41\u0e2d\u0e1b\u0e0b\u0e37\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e40\u0e01\u0e21 App Store \u0e08\u0e48\u0e32\u0e22\u0e07\u0e48\u0e32\u0e22\u0e46 \u0e43\u0e04\u0e23\u0e01\u0e47\u0e08\u0e48\u0e32\u0e22\u0e44\u0e14\u0e49\u0e14\u0e49\u0e27\u0e22 TrueMoney Wallet|date=2017-12-21|website=\u0e41\u0e2d\u0e1e\u0e14\u0e34\u0e2a\u0e04\u0e31\u0e2a|language=th|access-date=2019-06-06}}</ref>, Alipay, etc), users are able to pay with TrueMoney Wallet. There are currently over 200,000 accepted payment points for TrueMoney Wallet in Thailand.\n\nThe company also works with the Bank of Thailand, regulators, and the Royal Thai Police's Crime Suppression Division (CSD)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.naewna.com/likesara/401477|title=\u0e40\u0e15\u0e37\u0e2d\u0e19\u0e20\u0e31\u0e22! \u0e1b\u0e2d\u0e17.\u0e41\u0e09\u0e41\u0e01\u0e4a\u0e07\u0e41\u0e2a\u0e1a\u0e2b\u0e25\u0e2d\u0e01\u0e15\u0e38\u0e4b\u0e19\u0e40\u0e07\u0e34\u0e19 \u0e40\u0e1b\u0e34\u0e14\u0e40\u0e1e\u0e08\u2018\u0e1b\u0e25\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e22\u0e01\u0e39\u0e49\u0e19\u0e2d\u0e01\u0e23\u0e30\u0e1a\u0e1a-\u0e2d\u0e19\u0e38\u0e21\u0e31\u0e15\u0e34\u0e40\u0e23\u0e47\u0e27\u2019|website=https://www.naewna.com|language=th|access-date=2019-06-06}}</ref> to ensure TrueMoney Wallet has full compliance with regulatory frameworks, and reflect the brand's commitment to promote secure e-wallet usage and earn public trust.\n\nAcross the other five countries, TrueMoney offers financial services for underbanked consumers through its agent networks, which is located extensively in various cities and rural areas across each country. In 2018, TrueMoney Cambodia also launched its e-wallet app called \"TrueMoney app\", which enable users to make money transfer and various e-payment services easily from their mobile phone.\n\nIn Thailand, TrueMoney also offers international remittance service under the \"TrueMoney Transfer\" brand for Burmese and Cambodian migrant workers in Thailand to safely & quickly send money back home with consistent exchange rate and low fees.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n[[Category:Companies based in Bangkok]]\n[[Category:Financial services companies established in 2003]]\n[[Category:Financial services companies of Thailand]]\n[[Category:Mobile payments]]\n[[Category:Financial technology companies]]\n[[Category:Thai brands]]\n", "text_old": "{{COI|date=September 2016}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = TrueMoney\n| logo = TMN-LOGO.jpg\n| logo_size = 300px\n| type = [[Privately held company]]\n| area_served = 6 countries across Southeast Asia: Thailand, Cambodia, Myanmar, Vietnam, Indonesia and Philippines (as of 2019)\n| key_people = Tanyapong Thamavaranukupt (Co-President, Ascend Money)<br>\nMonsinee Nakapanant (Co-President, Ascend Money)\n| services = [[e-payment]]<br>[[mobile payment]]<br>[[digital banking]]\n| industry = [[Fintech]], [[Financial Services]]\n| num_employees = 700-1000\n| parent = [[Ascend Group]]<br>[[Ascend Money]]\n| foundation = 2003\n| location = Bangkok, Thailand\n| website = {{URL|http://www.ascendmoney.io|Ascend Money}}\n<br>{{URL|http://www.truemoney.com|TrueMoney Thailand}}<br>{{URL|http://www.truemoney.com.ph|TrueMoney Philippines}}<br>{{URL|http://www.truemoney.com.kh|TrueMoney Cambodia}}<br>{{URL|http://www.truemoney.co.id|TrueMoney Indonesia}}<br>{{URL|http://truemoneymyanmar.com/|TrueMoney Myanmar}}<br>{{URL|https://truemoney.com.vn/|TrueMoney Vietnam}}\n}}\n\n'''TrueMoney''' is a financial technology company in Southeast Asia with a mission to enable everyone to have access to financial services. \n\nThe company serves both digital and non digital customers in Thailand, Cambodia, Myanmar, Vietnam, Philippines, and Indonesia. TrueMoney has licenses to operate e-money in most Southeast Asian country.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bangkokpost.com/business/telecom/530175/true-money-makes-regional-moves|title=True Money makes regional moves &#124; Bangkok Post: business|date=2015-04-16|publisher=Bangkokpost.com|accessdate=2015-06-25}}</ref> \n\nOperated by its parent company Ascend Money and in partnership with Ant Financial (a subsidiary of Alibaba Group).\n\nAs of May 2019, the total processed value (TPV) of TrueMoney company was US$ 7.3 billion.\n\n==History==\nTrueMoney was originally founded in 2003 as part of [https://www3.truecorp.co.th/new/?ln=en True Corporation], but presently is operated by [https://www.ascendmoney.io/ Ascend Money] company, a subsidiary of [https://www.ascendcorp.com/ Ascend Group] - the digital technology arm of [http://www.cpgroupglobal.com/ Charoen Pokphand Group].  \n\nSince 1st November 2016, Ant Financial (Alipay) company invested in Ascend Money company.         This partnership aims to grow TrueMoney's technical expertise to strengthen its financial services eco-system for users and merchants<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2016/11/01/ant-financial-invests-in-thailands-ascent-money-as-part-of-global-expansion-play.html|title=Ant Financial invests in Thailand's Ascend Money as part of global expansion play|last=Choudhury|first=Saheli Roy|date=2016-11-01|website=CNBC|language=en|access-date=2019-06-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nationmultimedia.com/detail/Economy/30298894|title=Ascend Money links with Alibaba financial services unit|website=The Nation|language=en|access-date=2019-06-06}}</ref>\n\n==Services==\nIn Thailand, TrueMoney operates the \"TrueMoney Wallet\" brand (e-wallet application) that enable users to easily make online and offline payments (e.g. mobile/net top-ups, gaming top-ups, bill payments, peer-to-peer transfers, and QR-bar code scan retail payments) via using mobile phones.\n\nAs of 2019, the number of TrueMoney Wallet active annual users reached 8.4 million. \n\nBy leveraging on the brand's partnerships (e.g. 7-Eleven, popular F&B chains, online marketplace, street food vendors, etc), and world-class digital technology partners (e.g. Google<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bangkokpost.com/tech/local-news/1653488/truemoney-teams-up-with-google-play|title=TrueMoney teams up with Google Play|last=Limited|first=Bangkok Post Public Company|website=https://www.bangkokpost.com|access-date=2019-06-06}}</ref>, Apple<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.appdisqus.com/2017/12/21/truemoney-wallet-app-store-ios.html|title=\u0e0b\u0e37\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e41\u0e2d\u0e1b\u0e0b\u0e37\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e40\u0e01\u0e21 App Store \u0e08\u0e48\u0e32\u0e22\u0e07\u0e48\u0e32\u0e22\u0e46 \u0e43\u0e04\u0e23\u0e01\u0e47\u0e08\u0e48\u0e32\u0e22\u0e44\u0e14\u0e49\u0e14\u0e49\u0e27\u0e22 TrueMoney Wallet|date=2017-12-21|website=\u0e41\u0e2d\u0e1e\u0e14\u0e34\u0e2a\u0e04\u0e31\u0e2a|language=th|access-date=2019-06-06}}</ref>, Alipay, etc), users are able to pay with TrueMoney Wallet. There are currently over 200,000 accepted payment points for TrueMoney Wallet in Thailand.\n\nThe company also works with the Bank of Thailand, regulators, and the Royal Thai Police's Crime Suppression Division (CSD)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.naewna.com/likesara/401477|title=\u0e40\u0e15\u0e37\u0e2d\u0e19\u0e20\u0e31\u0e22! \u0e1b\u0e2d\u0e17.\u0e41\u0e09\u0e41\u0e01\u0e4a\u0e07\u0e41\u0e2a\u0e1a\u0e2b\u0e25\u0e2d\u0e01\u0e15\u0e38\u0e4b\u0e19\u0e40\u0e07\u0e34\u0e19 \u0e40\u0e1b\u0e34\u0e14\u0e40\u0e1e\u0e08\u2018\u0e1b\u0e25\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e22\u0e01\u0e39\u0e49\u0e19\u0e2d\u0e01\u0e23\u0e30\u0e1a\u0e1a-\u0e2d\u0e19\u0e38\u0e21\u0e31\u0e15\u0e34\u0e40\u0e23\u0e47\u0e27\u2019|website=https://www.naewna.com|language=th|access-date=2019-06-06}}</ref> to ensure TrueMoney Wallet has full compliance with regulatory frameworks, and reflect the brand's commitment to promote secure e-wallet usage and earn public trust.\n\nAcross the other five countries, TrueMoney offers financial services for underbanked consumers through its agent networks, which is located extensively in various cities and rural areas across each country. In 2018, TrueMoney Cambodia also launched its e-wallet app called \"TrueMoney app\", which enable users to make money transfer and various e-payment services easily from their mobile phone.\n\nIn Thailand, TrueMoney also offers international remittance service under the \"TrueMoney Transfer\" brand for Burmese and Cambodian migrant workers in Thailand to safely & quickly send money back home with consistent exchange rate and low fees.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n[[Category:Companies based in Bangkok]]\n[[Category:Financial services companies established in 2003]]\n[[Category:Financial services companies of Thailand]]\n[[Category:Mobile payments]]\n[[Category:Financial technology companies]]\n[[Category:Thai brands]]\n", "name_user": "37.111.1.119", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Ok)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TrueMoney"}
{"title_page": "Against All Odds (2019)", "text_new": "{{Infobox Wrestling event\n|name= Against All Odds (2019)\n|promotion= [[Impact Wrestling]]\n|date= February 17, 2019\n|date_aired  = March 29, 2019\n|venue= [[Sam's Town Hotel and Gambling Hall, Las Vegas|Sam\u2019s Town Casino]]\n|city= [[Las Vegas, Nevada]]\n|event= [[TNA Against All Odds|Against All Odds]]\n|nextevent2= Final\n|lastevent2= [[Against All Odds (2012)|2012]]\n|event2 = [[List of Impact! special episodes|''Impact!'' special episodes]]\n|lastevent3= Uncaged\n|nextevent3 = Fallout\n}}\n'''Against All Odds (2019)'''  was a [[professional wrestling]] television special produced by [[Impact Wrestling]], which took place on February 17, 2019 at [[Sam's Town Hotel and Gambling Hall, Las Vegas|Sam's Town Casino]] in [[Las Vegas, Nevada]]. It was the ninth event under the [[TNA Against All Odds|Against All Odds]] chronology. Unlike the previous events, this event was a special episode of the weekly ''[[Impact Wrestling (TV series)|Impact]]'' television broadcast on [[Pursuit Channel]] and [[Twitch (service)|Twitch]].\n\nThree [[mock combat|professional wrestling matches]] were contested at the event. The [[Card (sports)#Main event|main event]] featured [[Brian Cage]] taking on [[Killer Kross]], which Cage lost after interference by [[Johnny Impact]] and [[Taya Valkyrie]]. On the undercard, Valkyrie retained the [[Impact Knockouts Championship|Knockouts Championship]] against [[Jordynne Grace]] by getting counted out and [[Scarlett Bordeaux]] defeated [[Glenn Gilbertti]] in an intergender match.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Mike Killam |title=Impact Wrestling \u2018Against All Odds\u2019 Results (3/29): Brian Cage vs Killer Kross |url=https://www.prowrestling.com/impact-wrestling-against-all-odds-results-3-29-brian-cage-vs-killer-kross/ |website=Pro Wrestling.com |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=March 30, 2019}}</ref> The event featured the final appearance of [[Allie (wrestler)|Allie]] in Impact Wrestling.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Joe Anthony Myrick |title=Impact Wrestling: In defense of Allie\u2019s controversial death scene |url=https://dailyddt.com/2019/03/30/impact-wrestling-allie-death-scene-isnt-as-bad-as-you-think/ |website=Daily DDT |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=March 30, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=Greg Bush |title=Allie leaves Impact Wrestling, joins All Elite Wrestling |url=https://wrestling-edge.com/allie-leaves-impact-wrestling-joins-all-elite-wrestling/ |website=Wrestling Edge |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=March 21, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\n===Background===\n[[TNA Against All Odds|Against All Odds]] was held as a [[pay-per-view]] event by Impact Wrestling (then known as [[Total Nonstop Action Wrestling]]) between 2005 and 2012 until TNA discontinued most of its monthly pay-per-view events in 2013 in favor of the new pre-taped [[Impact One Night Only|One Night Only]] pay-per-view events.<ref>{{cite web |title=TNA Wrestling makes major changes to its PPV format for 2013 |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/tna-wrestling-makes-major-changes-to-its-ppv-format-for-2013-2013-1 |website=Business Insider |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=January 23, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=Brad Davis |title=TNA Only Running 4 Live Sunday Night PPVs In 2013 |url=https://www.sescoops.com/tna-announces-drastic-changes-to-ppv-strategy/ |website=SE Scoops |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=January 11, 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn November 8, 2018, Impact Wrestling announced the dates and venues of its February 2019 television tapings for ''[[Impact! (TV series)|Impact!]]'', with the tapings taking place between February 15 to February 17, 2019 at the [[Sam's Town Casino]] in [[Las Vegas, Nevada]].<ref>{{cite web |author1=Jerome Wilen |title=Impact announces first match for TV tapings in Las Vegas, Including a return in 2019 |url=https://www.wrestleview.com/impact-wrestling-news/118222-mpact-announces-first-match-for-tv-tapings-in-las-vegas/ |website=Wrestleview |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=November 9, 2018}}</ref> It was later announced that Against All Odds would return as a special episode of ''Impact!'' which would feature a portion of the February 17 tapings and would air on March 29.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Matt Boone |title=Preview For Tonight's Special \"Against All Odds\" Edition Of Impact Wrestling |url=https://ewrestling.com/article/preview-tonights-special-against-all-odds-edition-impact-wrestling |website=EWrestling |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=March 29, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Storylines===\n[[File:Taya Valkyrie 2-29-2020.jpg|thumb|right|180px|[[Taya Valkyrie]] was the defending [[Impact Knockouts Championship|Impact Knockouts Champion]] heading into Against All Odds.]]\nAt [[Impact Wrestling Homecoming|Homecoming]], [[Johnny Impact]] successfully defended the [[Impact World Championship]] against [[Brian Cage]] and [[Killer Kross]] attacked Impact and [[Taya Valkyrie]] after the match which concluded with Kross [[powerbomb]]ing Valkyrie into the crowd.<ref name=\"homecoming\">{{cite web |author1=WON/F4W |title=IMPACT HOMECOMING LIVE RESULTS: JOHNNY IMPACT VS. BRIAN CAGE |url=https://www.f4wonline.com/tna-results/impact-homecoming-live-results-johnny-impact-vs-brian-cage-273931 |website=Antonio Garza |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=January 6, 2019}}</ref> Cage continued to demand a rematch with Impact claiming that he was screwed out of the title while Kross and [[Moose (wrestler)|Moose]] also pursued the title, leading to a [[four-way match]] for the title at ''Uncaged'',<ref name=\"uncaged\">{{cite web |author1=Patches Chance |title=Impact Wrestling Uncaged Results and Review (February 15, 2019) |url=https://dailyddt.com/2019/02/16/impact-wrestling-uncaged-results-review/ |website=DDT Digest |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=February 16, 2019}}</ref> which Impact won to retain the title.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Antonio Garza |title=IMPACT WRESTLING UNCAGED RESULTS: TWO TITLE MATCHES, WORLD CUP |url=https://www.f4wonline.com/tna-results/impact-wrestling-uncaged-results-two-title-matches-world-cup-277106 |website=WON/F4W |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=February 15, 2019}}</ref> On the March 1 episode of ''Impact!'', Kross and Moose defeated Impact and Cage in a tag team match in which Cage was outnumbered due to Impact's injury.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Robert Gunier |title=Impact Wrestling Results (3/1): Johnny Impact & Brian Cage Vs. Moose & Killer Kross, Tessa Blanchard |url=https://www.wrestlinginc.com/news/2019/03/impact-wrestling-results-651521/ |website=Wrestling Inc. |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=March 2, 2019}}</ref> On the March 15 episode of ''Impact!'', Impact was set to defend the title against Cage but Kross instead brought out a downed Impact and Cage attacked him until Valkyrie turned on Cage by low blowing him and Impact then attacked Cage to reveal that it was a set up between Impact, Kross and Valkyrie to double cross Cage.<ref name=\"march15\">{{cite web |author1=Robert Gunier |title=Impact Wrestling Results (3/15): Johnny Impact Turns Heel, Tessa Blanchard Vs. Jordynne Grace |url=https://www.wrestlinginc.com/news/2019/03/impact-wrestling-results-652040/ |website=Wrestling Inc. |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=March 16, 2019}}</ref> It was later announced that Cage would face Kross in a match at Against All Odds.<ref name=\"preview\">{{cite web |author1=Mike Johnson |title=IMPACT WRESTLING AGAINST ALL ODDS PREVIEW FOR TONIGHT (NON SPOILER) |url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/125205/impact-wrestling-against-all-odds-preview-for-tonight-non-spoiler.html?p=1 |website=PW Insider |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=March 29, 2019}}</ref>\n\nAt Homecoming, [[Taya Valkyrie]] defeated [[Tessa Blanchard]] to win the [[Impact Knockouts Championship]].<ref name=\"homecoming\"/> Valkyrie successfully defended the title against Blanchard in a [[street fight]] at Uncaged.<ref name=\"uncaged\"/> Blanchard demanded a rematch for the title and it was announced that Blanchard would face [[Jordynne Grace]] in a match to determine the #1 contender for the Knockouts Championship on the March 15 episode of ''Impact!'', which Grace won,<ref name=\"march15\"/> thus setting up a match between Grace and Valkyrie for the Knockouts Championship at Against All Odds.<ref name=\"preview\"/>\n\nOn the March 8 episode of ''Impact!'', [[Scarlett Bordeaux]] declared herself the winner of her talent search and said that [[Disco Inferno (wrestler)|Glenn Gilbertti]]'s video was the most embarrassing, which led to Gilbertti insulting Bordeaux specifically and women's wrestling in general, claiming that women needed to stay at home and remain housewives and women's wrestling was nothing more than [[bra and panties match]]es, resulting in a confrontation between the two,<ref>{{cite web |author1=Robert Gunier |title=Impact Wrestling Results (3/8): Lucha Bros Vs. The Rascalz, The Dark War Ensues |url=https://www.wrestlinginc.com/news/2019/03/impact-wrestling-results-651781/ |website=Wrestling Inc. |accessdate=1 April 2020 |date=March 9, 2019}}</ref> leading to a match between the two at Against All Odds.<ref name=\"preview\"/>\n\n==Event==\n===Preliminary matches===\n[[File:Gail Kim Jan 2013.jpg|thumb|right|180px|[[Impact Hall of Fame]]r [[Gail Kim]] came out of retirement at Against All Odds to challenge [[Tessa Blanchard]] to a match at [[Rebellion (2019)|Rebellion]].]]\nThe event kicked off with an unsanctioned brawl between [[The Latin American Xchange]] ([[Santana and Ortiz]]) and [[The Lucha Brothers]] ([[Pentag\u00f3n Jr.]] and [[F\u00e9nix (wrestler)|F\u00e9nix]]). LAX would drive both members of Lucha Brothers through the tables and then [[Konnan]] challenged Lucha Brothers to a [[Full Metal Mayhem match]] for the [[Impact World Tag Team Championship|World Tag Team Championship]] at [[Rebellion (2019)|Rebellion]].\n\nNext was the opening match of the event between [[Glenn Gilbertti]] and [[Scarlett Bordeaux]]. As Gilbertti was hitting mounted punches to Bordeaux in the corner, Bordeaux countered by [[powerbomb]]ing him for the win.\n\nIt was followed by a confrontation between [[Gail Kim]] and [[Tessa Blanchard]], in which Blanchard demanded apology from Kim and her resignation from Impact Wrestling and Kim said that she resigned from Impact to take on Blanchard and challenged her to a match at Rebellion, which Blanchard accepted.\n\nNext was the penultimate match of the event, in which [[Taya Valkyrie]] defended the [[Impact Knockouts Championship|Knockouts Championship]] against [[Jordynne Grace]]. Grace avoided a [[moonsault]] by Valkyrie and attempted to nail a ''[[Professional wrestling throws#Half nelson driver|Grace Drive]]'' to Valkyrie but Valkyrie avoided it and then [[John Morrison (wrestler)|Johnny Impact]] checked on Valkyrie and took her backstage, thus causing her to get counted out. As a result, Grace won the match but Valkyrie retained the title.\n\n===Main event match===\n[[Brian Cage]] came out to confront Johnny Impact and Taya Valkyrie immediately after Valkyrie's match and tried to attack Impact until Cage's scheduled opponent [[Killer Kross]] attacked him from behind. Cage nailed a ''[[Facebuster#Fireman's carry facebuster|F5]]'' to Kross to pin him but Impact put Kross' foot on the ropes. The referee was distracted, allowing Valkyrie to hit a [[low blow]] to Cage and Kross delivered two ''[[Saito suplex|Doomsday Saitos]]'' to Cage and covered him for the pinfall but Cage kicked out and two but the referee still awarded the win to Kross and claimed that Cage's shoulders were down for the three count. Impact attacked Cage after the match.\n\nThe match was followed by a segment, in which [[Rosemary (wrestler)|Rosemary]] dragged [[Allie (wrestler)|Allie]] to the Undead Realm to retrieve her soul but [[Kiera Hogan]] intervened despite Rosemary's warning, which distracted Rosemary and allowed [[Su Yung]] in \"[[kayfabe|killing]]\" Allie.\n\n==Reception==\nAccording to Steph Franchomme of ''Vulture Hound'', ''Against All Odds'' \"was not the best special event\" but Impact \"definitely moved forward\" and \"took the right direction\", which could lead everyone \"to a major and unforgettable PPV ([[Rebellion (2019)|Rebellion]]).<ref>{{cite web |author1=Steph Franchomme |title=\u2018AGAINST ALL ODDS\u2019 REVIEW AND RESULTS \u2013 FROM THE IMPACT ZONE \u2013 SPECIAL EDITION \u2013 MARCH 29TH, 2019 |url=https://vulturehound.co.uk/2019/03/against-all-odds-review-and-results-from-the-impact-zone-special-edition-march-29th-2019/ |website=Vulture Hound |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=March 29, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Aftermath==\nMost of the matches and angles at Against All Odds led to the [[Rebellion (2019)|Rebellion]] pay-per-view event. Johnny Impact and Brian Cage continued their feud over the Impact World Championship, leading to a rematch between the two set for Rebellion.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Jeffrey Harris |title=Johnny Impact vs. Brian Cage Title Match Set for Rebellion |url=https://411mania.com/wrestling/johnny-impact-vs-brian-cage-rebellion/ |website=411 Mania |accessdate=1 April 2020 |date=March 23, 2019}}</ref> On the April 5 episode of ''Impact!'', Jordynne Grace earned herself a rematch for the Knockouts Championship at Rebellion by defeating the returning [[Madison Rayne]] to become the #1 contender for the title.<ref name=\"april5\">{{cite web |author1=Robert Gunier |title=Impact Wrestling Results (4/5): Madman Fulton's In-Ring Debut, Madison Rayne Returns To Impact |url=https://www.wrestlinginc.com/news/2019/04/impact-wrestling-results-652794/ |website=Wrestling Inc. |accessdate=1 April 2020 |date=April 6, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=Joseph Lee |title=Taya Valkyrie vs. Jordynne Grace Added To Impact Wrestling Rebellion, Updated Card |url=https://411mania.com/wrestling/taya-valkyrie-vs-jordynne-grace-added-to-impact-wrestling-rebellion-updated-card/ |website=411 Mania |accessdate=1 April 2020 |date=April 8, 2019}}</ref> The two teams collided in a mixed tag team match on the April 12 episode of ''Impact!'', where Impact and Valkyrie defeated Cage and Grace.<ref name=\"april12\">{{cite web |author1=Thomas Hall |title=Impact Wrestling Results \u2013 April 12, 2019 |url=https://wrestlingrumors.net/tommyhall/impact-wrestling-results-april-12-2019/ |website=Wrestling Rumors |accessdate=1 April 2020 |date=April 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\nRosemary vowed revenge on Kiera Hogan holding her responsible for Allie's \"demise\" and continued her feud with Su Yung over the next few weeks while continuing to berate Hogan for her actions.<ref name=\"april5\"/><ref name=\"april12\"/><ref>{{cite web |author1=Thomas Hall |title=Impact Wrestling Results \u2013 April 19, 2019 |url=https://wrestlingrumors.net/tommyhall/impact-wrestling-results-april-19-2019-2/ |website=Wrestling Rumors |accessdate=1 April 2020 |date=April 22, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=Thomas Hall |title=Impact Wrestling Results \u2013 April 26, 2019 |url=https://wrestlingrumors.net/tommyhall/impact-wrestling-results-april-26-2019/ |website=Wrestling Rumors |accessdate=1 April 2020 |date=April 28, 2019}}</ref> On the May 3 episode of ''Impact!'', Rosemary had a match with Hogan, which ended in a disqualification after Yung and her Undead Bridemaids interfered. Yung and the Undead Bridemaids attacked Rosemary after the match and Hogan turned on Rosemary by refusing to make the save for her.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Thomas Hall |title=Impact Wrestling Results \u2013 May 3, 2019 |url=https://wrestlingrumors.net/tommyhall/impact-wrestling-results-may-3-2019/ |website=Wrestling Rumors |accessdate=1 April 2020 |date=May 6, 2019}}</ref> Rosemary would then defeat Yung in a Demon Collar match on the May 17 episode of ''Impact!''.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Angel Carreras |title=Impact Wrestling Results (5/16): Swann Vs. Elgin, Kross Vs. Edwards, More |url=https://www.wrestlinginc.com/news/2019/05/impact-wrestling-live-ongoing-recap-654225/ |website=Wrestling Inc. |accessdate=1 April 2020 |date=May 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe Full Metal Mayhem match between Lucha Brothers and LAX for the World Tag Team Championship was made official for Rebellion.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Andrew Thompson |title=Lucha Bros Defending IMPACT Tag Titles Against LAX At 'Rebellion' In A Full Metal Mayhem Match |url=https://www.fightful.com/wrestling/lucha-bros-defending-impact-world-tag-team-titles-against-lax-rebellion-tlc-match |website=Fightful |accessdate=1 April 2020 |date=March 30, 2019}}</ref> Gail Kim's comeback match against Tessa Blanchard was also made official for Rebellion.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Jeremy Thomas |title=Gail Kim Returning to the Ring at Impact Rebellion |url=https://411mania.com/wrestling/gail-kim-returning-ring-impact-rebellion/ |website=411 Mania |accessdate=1 April 2020 |date=March 30, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Results==\n{{Pro Wrestling results table\n|times=<ref>{{cite web |title=Impact Wrestling #767 - Against All Odds 2019 |url=https://www.cagematch.net/?id=1&nr=227695 |website=Cagematch |accessdate=1 April 2020}}</ref>\n|match1  = [[Scarlett Bordeaux]] defeated [[Glenn Gilbertti]]\n|stip1   = [[Intergender wrestling|Intergender match]] \n|time1= 06:30\n|time2=12:45\n|time3=15:30\n|match2  = [[Jordynne Grace]] defeated [[Taya Valkyrie]] (c) by countout\n|stip2   =  [[Professional wrestling match types#Singles matches|Singles match]] for the [[Impact Knockouts Championship]] \n|match3  = [[Killer Kross]] defeated [[Brian Cage]]\n|stip3   = Singles match\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{TNAPPV|Against All Odds}}\n\n[[Category:TNA Against All Odds]]\n[[Category:2019 in professional wrestling]]\n[[Category:February 2019 sports events in the United States]]\n[[Category:Professional wrestling in Nevada]]\n[[Category:2019 in Nevada]]\n[[Category:2019 American television episodes]]\n[[Category:2010s American television specials]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Wrestling event\n|name= Against All Odds (2019)\n|promotion= [[Impact Wrestling]]\n|date= February 17, 2019\n|date_aired  = March 29, 2019\n|venue= [[Sam's Town Hotel and Gambling Hall, Las Vegas|Sam\u2019s Town Casino]]\n|city= [[Las Vegas, Nevada]]\n|event= [[TNA Against All Odds|Against All Odds]]\n|nextevent2= Final\n|lastevent2= [[Against All Odds (2012)|2012]]\n|event2 = [[List of Impact! special episodes|''Impact!'' special episodes]]\n|lastevent3= Uncaged\n|nextevent3 = Fallout\n}}\n'''Against All Odds (2019)'''  was a [[professional wrestling]] television special produced by [[Impact Wrestling]], which took place on February 17, 2019 at [[Sam's Town Hotel and Gambling Hall, Las Vegas|Sam\u2019s Town Casino]] in [[Las Vegas, Nevada]]. It was the ninth event under the [[TNA Against All Odds|Against All Odds]] chronology. Unlike the previous events, this event was a special episode of the weekly ''[[Impact Wrestling (TV series)|Impact]]'' television broadcast on [[Pursuit Channel]] and [[Twitch (service)|Twitch]].\n\nThree [[mock combat|professional wrestling matches]] were contested at the event. The [[Card (sports)#Main event|main event]] featured [[Brian Cage]] taking on [[Killer Kross]], which Cage lost after interference by [[Johnny Impact]] and [[Taya Valkyrie]]. On the undercard, Valkyrie retained the [[Impact Knockouts Championship|Knockouts Championship]] against [[Jordynne Grace]] by getting counted out and [[Scarlett Bordeaux]] defeated [[Glenn Gilbertti]] in an intergender match.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Mike Killam |title=Impact Wrestling \u2018Against All Odds\u2019 Results (3/29): Brian Cage vs Killer Kross |url=https://www.prowrestling.com/impact-wrestling-against-all-odds-results-3-29-brian-cage-vs-killer-kross/ |website=Pro Wrestling.com |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=March 30, 2019}}</ref> The event featured the final appearance of [[Allie (wrestler)|Allie]] in Impact Wrestling.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Joe Anthony Myrick |title=Impact Wrestling: In defense of Allie\u2019s controversial death scene |url=https://dailyddt.com/2019/03/30/impact-wrestling-allie-death-scene-isnt-as-bad-as-you-think/ |website=Daily DDT |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=March 30, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=Greg Bush |title=Allie leaves Impact Wrestling, joins All Elite Wrestling |url=https://wrestling-edge.com/allie-leaves-impact-wrestling-joins-all-elite-wrestling/ |website=Wrestling Edge |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=March 21, 2019}}</ref>\n==Production==\n===Background===\n[[TNA Against All Odds|Against All Odds]] was held as a [[pay-per-view]] event by Impact Wrestling (then known as [[Total Nonstop Action Wrestling]]) between 2005 and 2012 until TNA discontinued most of its monthly pay-per-view events in 2013 in favor of the new pre-taped [[Impact One Night Only|One Night Only]] pay-per-view events.<ref>{{cite web |title=TNA Wrestling makes major changes to its PPV format for 2013 |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/tna-wrestling-makes-major-changes-to-its-ppv-format-for-2013-2013-1 |website=Business Insider |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=January 23, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=Brad Davis |title=TNA Only Running 4 Live Sunday Night PPVs In 2013 |url=https://www.sescoops.com/tna-announces-drastic-changes-to-ppv-strategy/ |website=SE Scoops |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=January 11, 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn November 8, 2018, Impact Wrestling announced the dates and venues of its February 2019 television tapings for ''[[Impact! (TV series)|Impact!]]'', with the tapings taking place between February 15 to February 17, 2019 at the [[Sam's Town Casino]] in [[Las Vegas, Nevada]].<ref>{{cite web |author1=Jerome Wilen |title=Impact announces first match for TV tapings in Las Vegas, Including a return in 2019 |url=https://www.wrestleview.com/impact-wrestling-news/118222-mpact-announces-first-match-for-tv-tapings-in-las-vegas/ |website=Wrestleview |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=November 9, 2018}}</ref> It was later announced that Against All Odds would return as a special episode of ''Impact!'' which would feature a portion of the February 17 tapings and would air on March 29.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Matt Boone |title=Preview For Tonight's Special \"Against All Odds\" Edition Of Impact Wrestling |url=https://ewrestling.com/article/preview-tonights-special-against-all-odds-edition-impact-wrestling |website=EWrestling |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=March 29, 2019}}</ref>\n===Storylines===\n[[File:Taya Valkyrie 2-29-2020.jpg|thumb|right|180px|[[Taya Valkyrie]] was the defending [[Impact Knockouts Championship|Impact Knockouts Champion]] heading into Against All Odds.]]\nAt [[Impact Wrestling Homecoming|Homecoming]], [[Johnny Impact]] successfully defended the [[Impact World Championship]] against [[Brian Cage]] and [[Killer Kross]] attacked Impact and [[Taya Valkyrie]] after the match which concluded with Kross [[powerbomb]]ing Valkyrie into the crowd.<ref name=\"homecoming\">{{cite web |author1=WON/F4W |title=IMPACT HOMECOMING LIVE RESULTS: JOHNNY IMPACT VS. BRIAN CAGE |url=https://www.f4wonline.com/tna-results/impact-homecoming-live-results-johnny-impact-vs-brian-cage-273931 |website=Antonio Garza |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=January 6, 2019}}</ref> Cage continued to demand a rematch with Impact claiming that he was screwed out of the title while Kross and [[Moose (wrestler)|Moose]] also pursued the title, leading to a [[four-way match]] for the title at ''Uncaged'',<ref name=\"uncaged\">{{cite web |author1=Patches Chance |title=Impact Wrestling Uncaged Results and Review (February 15, 2019) |url=https://dailyddt.com/2019/02/16/impact-wrestling-uncaged-results-review/ |website=DDT Digest |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=February 16, 2019}}</ref> which Impact won to retain the title.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Antonio Garza |title=IMPACT WRESTLING UNCAGED RESULTS: TWO TITLE MATCHES, WORLD CUP |url=https://www.f4wonline.com/tna-results/impact-wrestling-uncaged-results-two-title-matches-world-cup-277106 |website=WON/F4W |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=February 15, 2019}}</ref> On the March 1 episode of ''Impact!'', Kross and Moose defeated Impact and Cage in a tag team match in which Cage was outnumbered due to Impact's injury.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Robert Gunier |title=Impact Wrestling Results (3/1): Johnny Impact & Brian Cage Vs. Moose & Killer Kross, Tessa Blanchard |url=https://www.wrestlinginc.com/news/2019/03/impact-wrestling-results-651521/ |website=Wrestling Inc. |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=March 2, 2019}}</ref> On the March 15 episode of ''Impact!'', Impact was set to defend the title against Cage but Kross instead brought out a downed Impact and Cage attacked him until Valkyrie turned on Cage by low blowing him and Impact then attacked Cage to reveal that it was a set up between Impact, Kross and Valkyrie to double cross Cage.<ref name=\"march15\">{{cite web |author1=Robert Gunier |title=Impact Wrestling Results (3/15): Johnny Impact Turns Heel, Tessa Blanchard Vs. Jordynne Grace |url=https://www.wrestlinginc.com/news/2019/03/impact-wrestling-results-652040/ |website=Wrestling Inc. |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=March 16, 2019}}</ref> It was later announced that Cage would face Kross in a match at Against All Odds.<ref name=\"preview\">{{cite web |author1=Mike Johnson |title=IMPACT WRESTLING AGAINST ALL ODDS PREVIEW FOR TONIGHT (NON SPOILER) |url=https://www.pwinsider.com/article/125205/impact-wrestling-against-all-odds-preview-for-tonight-non-spoiler.html?p=1 |website=PW Insider |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=March 29, 2019}}</ref>\n\nAt Homecoming, [[Taya Valkyrie]] defeated [[Tessa Blanchard]] to win the [[Impact Knockouts Championship]].<ref name=\"homecoming\"/> Valkyrie successfully defended the title against Blanchard in a [[street fight]] at Uncaged.<ref name=\"uncaged\"/> Blanchard demanded a rematch for the title and it was announced that Blanchard would face [[Jordynne Grace]] in a match to determine the #1 contender for the Knockouts Championship on the March 15 episode of ''Impact!'', which Grace won,<ref name=\"march15\"/> thus setting up a match between Grace and Valkyrie for the Knockouts Championship at Against All Odds.<ref name=\"preview\"/>\n\nOn the March 8 episode of ''Impact!'', [[Scarlett Bordeaux]] declared herself the winner of her talent search and said that [[Disco Inferno (wrestler)|Glenn Gilbertti]]'s video was the most embarrassing, which led to Gilbertti insulting Bordeaux specifically and women's wrestling in general, claiming that women needed to stay at home and remain housewives and women's wrestling was nothing more than [[bra and panties match]]es, resulting in a confrontation between the two,<ref>{{cite web |author1=Robert Gunier |title=Impact Wrestling Results (3/8): Lucha Bros Vs. The Rascalz, The Dark War Ensues |url=https://www.wrestlinginc.com/news/2019/03/impact-wrestling-results-651781/ |website=Wrestling Inc. |accessdate=1 April 2020 |date=March 9, 2019}}</ref> leading to a match between the two at Against All Odds.<ref name=\"preview\"/>\n\n==Event==\n===Preliminary matches===\n[[File:Gail Kim Jan 2013.jpg|thumb|right|180px|[[Impact Hall of Fame]]r [[Gail Kim]] came out of retirement at Against All Odds to challenge [[Tessa Blanchard]] to a match at [[Rebellion (2019)|Rebellion]].]]\nThe event kicked off with an unsanctioned brawl between [[The Latin American Xchange]] ([[Santana and Ortiz]]) and [[The Lucha Brothers]] ([[Pentag\u00f3n Jr.]] and [[F\u00e9nix (wrestler)|F\u00e9nix]]). LAX would drive both members of Lucha Brothers through the tables and then [[Konnan]] challenged Lucha Brothers to a [[Full Metal Mayhem match]] for the [[Impact World Tag Team Championship|World Tag Team Championship]] at [[Rebellion (2019)|Rebellion]].\n\nNext was the opening match of the event between [[Glenn Gilbertti]] and [[Scarlett Bordeaux]]. As Gilbertti was hitting mounted punches to Bordeaux in the corner, Bordeaux countered by [[powerbomb]]ing him for the win.\n\nIt was followed by a confrontation between [[Gail Kim]] and [[Tessa Blanchard]], in which Blanchard demanded apology from Kim and her resignation from Impact Wrestling and Kim said that she resigned from Impact to take on Blanchard and challenged her to a match at Rebellion, which Blanchard accepted.\n\nNext was the penultimate match of the event, in which [[Taya Valkyrie]] defended the [[Impact Knockouts Championship|Knockouts Championship]] against [[Jordynne Grace]]. Grace avoided a [[moonsault]] by Valkyrie and attempted to nail a ''[[Professional wrestling throws#Half nelson driver|Grace Drive]]'' to Valkyrie but Valkyrie avoided it and then [[John Morrison (wrestler)|Johnny Impact]] checked on Valkyrie and took her backstage, thus causing her to get counted out. As a result, Grace won the match but Valkyrie retained the title.\n\n===Main event match===\n[[Brian Cage]] came out to confront Johnny Impact and Taya Valkyrie immediately after Valkyrie's match and tried to attack Impact until Cage's scheduled opponent [[Killer Kross]] attacked him from behind. Cage nailed a ''[[Facebuster#Fireman's carry facebuster|F5]]'' to Kross to pin him but Impact put Kross' foot on the ropes. The referee was distracted, allowing Valkyrie to hit a [[low blow]] to Cage and Kross delivered two ''[[Saito suplex|Doomsday Saitos]]'' to Cage and covered him for the pinfall but Cage kicked out and two but the referee still awarded the win to Kross and claimed that Cage's shoulders were down for the three count. Impact attacked Cage after the match.\n\nThe match was followed by a segment, in which [[Rosemary (wrestler)|Rosemary]] dragged [[Allie (wrestler)|Allie]] to the Undead Realm to retrieve her soul but [[Kiera Hogan]] intervened despite Rosemary's warning, which distracted Rosemary and allowed [[Su Yung]] in \"[[kayfabe|killing]]\" Allie.\n\n==Reception==\nAccording to Steph Franchomme of ''Vulture Hound'', ''Against All Odds'' \"was not the best special event\" but Impact \"definitely moved forward\" and \"took the right direction\", which could lead everyone \"to a major and unforgettable PPV ([[Rebellion (2019)|Rebellion]]).<ref>{{cite web |author1=Steph Franchomme |title=\u2018AGAINST ALL ODDS\u2019 REVIEW AND RESULTS \u2013 FROM THE IMPACT ZONE \u2013 SPECIAL EDITION \u2013 MARCH 29TH, 2019 |url=https://vulturehound.co.uk/2019/03/against-all-odds-review-and-results-from-the-impact-zone-special-edition-march-29th-2019/ |website=Vulture Hound |accessdate=31 March 2020 |date=March 29, 2019}}</ref>\n==Aftermath==\nMost of the matches and angles at Against All Odds led to the [[Rebellion (2019)|Rebellion]] pay-per-view event. Johnny Impact and Brian Cage continued their feud over the Impact World Championship, leading to a rematch between the two set for Rebellion.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Jeffrey Harris |title=Johnny Impact vs. Brian Cage Title Match Set for Rebellion |url=https://411mania.com/wrestling/johnny-impact-vs-brian-cage-rebellion/ |website=411 Mania |accessdate=1 April 2020 |date=March 23, 2019}}</ref> On the April 5 episode of ''Impact!'', Jordynne Grace earned herself a rematch for the Knockouts Championship at Rebellion by defeating the returning [[Madison Rayne]] to become the #1 contender for the title.<ref name=\"april5\">{{cite web |author1=Robert Gunier |title=Impact Wrestling Results (4/5): Madman Fulton's In-Ring Debut, Madison Rayne Returns To Impact |url=https://www.wrestlinginc.com/news/2019/04/impact-wrestling-results-652794/ |website=Wrestling Inc. |accessdate=1 April 2020 |date=April 6, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=Joseph Lee |title=Taya Valkyrie vs. Jordynne Grace Added To Impact Wrestling Rebellion, Updated Card |url=https://411mania.com/wrestling/taya-valkyrie-vs-jordynne-grace-added-to-impact-wrestling-rebellion-updated-card/ |website=411 Mania |accessdate=1 April 2020 |date=April 8, 2019}}</ref> The two teams collided in a mixed tag team match on the April 12 episode of ''Impact!'', where Impact and Valkyrie defeated Cage and Grace.<ref name=\"april12\">{{cite web |author1=Thomas Hall |title=Impact Wrestling Results \u2013 April 12, 2019 |url=https://wrestlingrumors.net/tommyhall/impact-wrestling-results-april-12-2019/ |website=Wrestling Rumors |accessdate=1 April 2020 |date=April 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\nRosemary vowed revenge on Kiera Hogan holding her responsible for Allie's \"demise\" and continued her feud with Su Yung over the next few weeks while continuing to berate Hogan for her actions.<ref name=\"april5\"/><ref name=\"april12\"/><ref>{{cite web |author1=Thomas Hall |title=Impact Wrestling Results \u2013 April 19, 2019 |url=https://wrestlingrumors.net/tommyhall/impact-wrestling-results-april-19-2019-2/ |website=Wrestling Rumors |accessdate=1 April 2020 |date=April 22, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=Thomas Hall |title=Impact Wrestling Results \u2013 April 26, 2019 |url=https://wrestlingrumors.net/tommyhall/impact-wrestling-results-april-26-2019/ |website=Wrestling Rumors |accessdate=1 April 2020 |date=April 28, 2019}}</ref> On the May 3 episode of ''Impact!'', Rosemary had a match with Hogan, which ended in a disqualification after Yung and her Undead Bridemaids interfered. Yung and the Undead Bridemaids attacked Rosemary after the match and Hogan turned on Rosemary by refusing to make the save for her.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Thomas Hall |title=Impact Wrestling Results \u2013 May 3, 2019 |url=https://wrestlingrumors.net/tommyhall/impact-wrestling-results-may-3-2019/ |website=Wrestling Rumors |accessdate=1 April 2020 |date=May 6, 2019}}</ref> Rosemary would then defeat Yung in a Demon Collar match on the May 17 episode of ''Impact!''.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Angel Carreras |title=Impact Wrestling Results (5/16): Swann Vs. Elgin, Kross Vs. Edwards, More |url=https://www.wrestlinginc.com/news/2019/05/impact-wrestling-live-ongoing-recap-654225/ |website=Wrestling Inc. |accessdate=1 April 2020 |date=May 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe Full Metal Mayhem match between Lucha Brothers and LAX for the World Tag Team Championship was made official for Rebellion.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Andrew Thompson |title=Lucha Bros Defending IMPACT Tag Titles Against LAX At 'Rebellion' In A Full Metal Mayhem Match |url=https://www.fightful.com/wrestling/lucha-bros-defending-impact-world-tag-team-titles-against-lax-rebellion-tlc-match |website=Fightful |accessdate=1 April 2020 |date=March 30, 2019}}</ref> Gail Kim's comeback match against Tessa Blanchard was also made official for Rebellion.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Jeremy Thomas |title=Gail Kim Returning to the Ring at Impact Rebellion |url=https://411mania.com/wrestling/gail-kim-returning-ring-impact-rebellion/ |website=411 Mania |accessdate=1 April 2020 |date=March 30, 2019}}</ref>\n==Results==\n{{Pro Wrestling results table\n|times=<ref>{{cite web |title=Impact Wrestling #767 - Against All Odds 2019 |url=https://www.cagematch.net/?id=1&nr=227695 |website=Cagematch |accessdate=1 April 2020}}</ref>\n|match1  = [[Scarlett Bordeaux]] defeated [[Glenn Gilbertti]]\n|stip1   = [[Intergender wrestling|Intergender match]] \n|time1= 06:30\n|time2=12:45\n|time3=15:30\n|match2  = [[Jordynne Grace]] defeated [[Taya Valkyrie]] (c) by countout\n|stip2   =  [[Professional wrestling match types#Singles matches|Singles match]] for the [[Impact Knockouts Championship]] \n|match3  = [[Killer Kross]] defeated [[Brian Cage]]\n|stip3   = Singles match\n}}\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{TNAPPV|Against All Odds}}\n[[Category:TNA Against All Odds]]\n[[Category:2019 in professional wrestling]]\n[[Category:February 2019 sports events in the United States]]\n[[Category:Professional wrestling in Nevada]]\n[[Category:2019 in Nevada]]\n[[Category:2019 American television episodes]]\n[[Category:2010s American television specials]]\n", "name_user": "CAPTAIN RAJU", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up,typo(s) fixed: \u2019s \u2192 's", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Against_All_Odds_(2019)"}
{"title_page": "Uwe Nolte", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2016}}\n{{BLP sources |date=November 2016}}\n\n'''Uwe Nolte''' (born 11 May 1969 in [[Merseburg]]) is a German poet, musician and [[graphic artist]].\n\n== Life and work ==\n\nUwe Nolte is a contemporary German poet. His work is an attempt to translate the concerns and aesthetics of German Romanticism into the present age. Formally orientated on traditional role models such as [[Joseph von Eichendorff]] and [[Nikolaus Lenau]], his poetry is characterised by emotional depth and tenderness, archaic imagery and a fast-paced rhythm. Nolte frequently approaches the contemporary world and personal experiences through ancient symbols, myths, historical figures and nature.<ref>http://artisttrove.com/artist/204042230518/Orplid+-official-</ref>\n\nNolte was born and raised in the town of Merseburg. The city is known for the \"[[Merseburger Zauberspr\u00fcche]]\", a set of ancient healing incantations from the Germanic pagan era, which has crucially shaped Nolte's understanding of the purpose of poetry and art.\n\nBorn in 1969, Nolte grew up in the formerly Soviet-occupied Eastern part of Germany (GDR). Like many East Germans who were disillusioned with the GDR's ideologically constrained education system, Nolte is entirely self-taught. Major influences on his artistic development were [[Friedrich H\u00f6lderlin]], [[Jakob B\u00f6hme]] and [[Friedrich Nietzsche]]. At the age of 21, he served as a soldier at the German-German frontier, where he refused to shoot at fellow Germans who tried to escape from the Soviet- to the US-occupied sector. Unpleasant experiences with the foreign imposed Soviet system did not prevent Nolte from developing a fascination with Russian culture and landscape. In 2011, Nolte moved to [[Samara, Russia|Samara]] with his former partner and fellow artist of Russian-German ancestry, Kristina Zieber. Nolte remains deeply impressed with the archaic and sometimes brute force he encountered in the Russian wilderness, where \"powerful spirits are still alive, forming an essential part of people's daily lives.\" Nolte's Russian experience is reflected in his recent poetry collection \"Falke Heime\".<ref></http://www.vkonline.ru/article/20319.html</ref>\n\nAccording to a family legend, Nolte's lineage on his mother's side goes back to the Protestant reformer [[Martin Luther]].\n\n== Music ==\n\nMusic is an integral part of Nolte's life and creative path. His poetry has been set to music by independent artists from his home region, such as [[Forseti (band)|Forseti]] from Jena. Nolte himself has been involved in several music projects, such as Barditus, Sonnentau and [[Orplid]] (with Frank Machau). The soundscape of Orplid is experimental, with links to [[Neofolk]] and Neoclassical music. It draws inspiration from the main currents of the German tradition: Germanic and Greek mythology, medieval Christian symbolism, 19th century Romanticism, and the all-pervasive notion of the sanctity of nature. The name of the band is taken from the opening line of the poem \"Gesang Weylas\"<ref>http://www.mumag.de/gedichte/moe_e10.html</ref> (Weyla's Song) by 19th-century Swabian poet [[Eduard M\u00f6rike]]: \"Du bist Orplid, mein Land.\" (You are Orplid, my land). The music is based on lyrics by Nolte and other German poets, such as [[Friedrich Schiller]], [[Annette von Droste-H\u00fclshoff]], Joseph von Eichendorff, [[Gottfried Benn]], [[Oda Schaefer]], [[Frank Wedekind]] and Rolf Schilling. Orplid have rendered a musical interpretation of the \"Merseburg Incantations\" in overtone singing, which Nolte learned from shamans in Russia.\n \nIn his youth, Nolte was an ardent fan of [[Manowar]], as reflected in his humorous tribute poem, \"Manowar\" (Falke Heime, 2016). Records by Western bands were extremely difficult to get hold of during the Soviet occupation, with record prices as high as half a month's rent. The ecstatic dynamism of [[Heavy metal music|Heavy Metal]] has never left him, Nolte explains. Orplid have a large following in the underground music scene.\n\n== Discography ==\n\n* 1997: Orplid (CD)\n* 1998: Heimkehr (CD)\n* 1998: Das Schicksal (Vinyl)\n* 1999: Geheiligt sei der Toten Name (MCD)\n* 2000: Orplid (CD-Re-Edition)\n* 2000: Barbarossa (Vinyl)\n* 2002: N\u00e4chtliche J\u00fcnger (CD)\n* 2002: N\u00e4chtliche J\u00fcnger (Vinyl)\n* 2006: Sterbender Satyr (CD)\n* 2007: Fr\u00fche Werke (CD)\n* 2007: Fr\u00fche Werke (CD-Specialedition)\n* 2008: Greifenherz (CD)\n\n;NolteX releases\n* 1994: R\u00fcckgrat, \"Am Tage des Herrn\" (MC)\n* 1996: R\u00fcckgrat, \"Freude und Leid\" (MC)\n* 2003: Sonnentau, \"Das Laub f\u00e4llt von den B\u00e4umen\" (Vinyl/Prophecy Prod.)\n* 2004: R\u00fcckgrat \"Freude und Leid\" (CD)\n* 2004: Barditus, \"Die letzten Goten\" (MCD)\n* 2004: Barditus, \"Schwarzer Heiland\" (MCD)\n* 2005: Eichendorff, \"Liedersammlung\" (CD u. a. mit [[Forseti (band)|Forseti]], [[Sonne Hagal]], Waldteufel \n* 2006: Diverse, \"Forseti lebt\" (CD u. a. mit [[Death in June]], Waldteufel)\n* 2008: [[Rolf Schilling]], \"Gesang \u00fcberm Quell\" (CD)\n\n;Compilations\n* R\u00fcckgrat, \"Der Freie Wille\" (Riefenstahl-Sampler)\n* Der G\u00f6tter Gnade (Black-Magazin)\n* Ewig unbewegt (Cavalcare la Tigre)\n* Fr\u00fchling/Wille und Tat (Das Graue Corps)\n* Jenseits von hier (Miroque VI)\n* Stille I (Lichttaufe)\n* S\u00f6hne des Ares (To Magic II)\n* Das M\u00e4dchen aus der Fremde (Kenotaph)\n* Dort in moosumrankten Kl\u00fcften + Abendlich rauscht schon der Wald (Eichendorff-Liedersammlung)\n* Stille II (Looking for Europe)\n* Die Seherin (Orkus-Magazin)\n* Auf deine Lider senk ich Schlummer (Gothic Spirits)\n\n== Cover songs ==\n* Forseti, \"Am Abend\" (CD \"Jenzig\")\n* Forseti, \"Letzter Traum\", (CD \"Windzeit\")\n* Forseti, \"Herbstabend\", (CD \"Windzeit\")<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ewdxaGkEI_k</ref>\n* Forseti, \"M\u00fcder Wanderer\", (CD \"Erde\")<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OHWM9smQYAk</ref>\n* Forseti, \"Das Abendland\", (CD \"Erde\")\n* [[Von Thronstahl]], \"Noch bl\u00fcht im Geist verborgen\", (CD \"Imperium internum\") \n* Stein, \"Blume auf dem Felsenschorf\", (CD \"Am Feld\")<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tJecHEBzfFI</ref>\n* Christian Glowatzki, \"Lied zur Nacht\", (CD \"Die Zeit legt ab ihr altes Kleid\")<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FwrxwTZlyoA</ref>\n* Stern des Bundes, \"Lichtmess\", (CD \"NolteX-Werkschau\")\n* Sonnenkind, \"Flechte Blumen dir ins Haar\", (CD \"NolteX-Werkschau\")<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5Uluy1Oef_4</ref>\n\n== Exhibitions ==\n* 1996, Halle (D), Galerie am Eselsbrunnen\n* 2004, Heldrungen (D), Wasserburg\n* 2005, Portland (USA), Galerie \"Heathen Art\"<ref>http://www.hexmagazine.com/heathen_art.html</ref>\n* 2005, Halle (D), Galerie \"Kontaktart\"\n* 2010, Samara (RU), Galerie \"Babylon\"\n* 2011, Suhl (D), Kultur- und Kongre\u00dfzentrum<ref>http://www.dtoday.de/regionen/lokal-panorama_artikel,-Ausstellung-%E2%80%9EFantaFiction-%E2%80%93-Fantastische-Malerei-Zeichnung-und-Plastik%E2%80%9C-_arid,90927.html</ref>\n* 2013, Merseburg (D), Kunststiftung \"Ben zi Bena\"\n* 2015, R\u00fcbeland (D), Kreuzm\u00fchle\n\n== Books ==\n* Erik Zimmer (Hrsg.): ''Jugend dichtet. Poems of the youth.'' Ursprung-Verlag, F\u00fcrth i. Odw. 1990, {{ISBN|3-9800309-7-0}}.\n* Michael K. Brust, Gerald H\u00f6fer: ''Tief im Scho\u00dfe des Kyffh\u00e4users.'' Anthology. Arte Fakt Verlagsanstalt, Dresden/ Bendeleben 2004, {{ISBN|3-937364-04-8}}.\n* Andreas Diesel, Dieter Gerten: ''Looking for Europe \u2013 Neofolk und Hintergr\u00fcnde.'' Zeltingen-Rachtig 2005, {{ISBN|3-936878-02-1}}.\n* Arnshaugk: ''Ein Lesebuch.'' Anthology. Verlag Arnshaugk, 2009, {{ISBN|978-3-926370-36-5}}.\n* ''Das Lindenblatt.'' Anthology. Verlag Arnshaugk, 2011, {{ISBN|978-3-926370-55-6}}.\n* ''Das Lindenblatt.'' Anthology. Verlag Arnshaugk, 2012, {{ISBN|978-3-926370-83-9}}.\n* ''Das Lindenblatt.'' Anthology. Verlag Arnshaugk, 2014, {{ISBN|