 Dreams'' which was shown at the ''Pornfilmfestival Berlin'' and which won the [[Eroticline Award]] for 'Best German Film' one year later.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.erotikgigant.com/pornonews/307-eline-award-gewinner-der-venus-berlin-2008 |title=Eroticline Awards winner of 2008 |access-date=2011-05-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110630034954/http://www.erotikgigant.com/pornonews/307-eline-award-gewinner-der-venus-berlin-2008 |archive-date=2011-06-30 |url-status=dead }}</ref> From 2007 to 2008, he was filmed for a [[documentary]] about his life called ''Till Kraemer \u2013 Buddhist and Porn Star'', which was produced by Ulrike Zimmermann. The documentary is currently in [[post production]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.cinando.com/DefaultController.aspx?PageID=FicheFilm&IdC=2070&IdF=42334 |title=Till Kraemer \u2013 Buddhist and Porn Star |access-date=2016-03-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160314031226/http://www.cinando.com/DefaultController.aspx?PageID=FicheFilm&IdC=2070&IdF=42334 |archive-date=2016-03-14 |url-status=live }}</ref> In 2008, Kraemer co-hosted the erotic call-in show ''La Notte'' with Leonie Saint on [[9Live]].<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1231013/ La Notte], episode dated 9 May 2008</ref> He also began to work as a [[Trance music|Trance]] [[disc jockey]].<ref>[http://de.till-kraemer.com/presse/pressespiegel/coupe/images/sex_mit_dem_plattenteller.jpg \u201eSex mit dem Plattenteller?\u201c], ''Coup\u00e9'' magazine 08/2008</ref>\n\nIn July 2009, Kraemer started to work as a film critic for ''Coup\u00e9''. Through the February 2011 issue, he wrote reviews for four films and four [[DVD]]s.<ref>''Coup\u00e9'', issue 08/2009, July 31, 2009</ref> His reviews also appeared in a German [[car tuning]] magazine called ''0-100 Street Performance''.<ref name=\"0-100\">''0-100 Street Performance'', issue July & August 2009 (04/09), page 30-33</ref>\n\nIn December 2009, the book ''Alles \u00fcber Porno!'' by Marcel Feige was